[
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Matthew Henry's Concise Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "103:15-18 How short is man's life, and uncertain! The flower of the garden is commonly more choice, and will last the longer, for being sheltered by the garden-wall, and the gardener's care; but the flower of the field, to which life is here compared, is not only withering in itself, but exposed to the cold blasts, and liable to be cropt and trod on by the beasts of the field. Such is man. God considers this, and pities him; let him consider it himself. God's mercy is better than life, for it will outlive it. His righteousness, the truth of his promise, shall be unto children's children, who tread in the footsteps of their forefathers' piety. Then shall mercy be preserved to them.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Barnes' Notes on the Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "As for man - literally, \"Man; like the grass are his days!\" The thought is fixed on man: man so frail and weak; man, not only made originally of earth, but man delicate, feeble, soon to pass away like the springing grass, or like the fading flower.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "His days are as grass - See the notes at Psalm 90:5-6; compare Isaiah 40:6-8, notes; 1 Peter 1:24, note.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "His days are as grass - See the notes at ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Psalm 90:5-6",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "; compare ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Isaiah 40:6-8",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ", notes; ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1 Peter 1:24",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ", note.",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "As a flower of the field - As a blossom. It opens with beauty and fragrance, but soon fades and perishes.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "So he flourisheth - Rather, \"So he blossoms.\" That is, he is like a flower that is fresh and beautiful, and that soon withers away. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "So he flourisheth - Rather, \"So he blossoms.\" That is, he is like a flower that is fresh and beautiful, and that soon withers away. ",
            "children": []
